description._content: Catalog #: NI-029 Notes:Display of Army aircraft at the Rockwell Field Air Depot circa 1930 at North Island. Dirigible hangar to the left was part of NAS San Diego. Aircraft left to right are three Keystone B-4 bombers, three Curtiss O-1 Falcons, four Curtiss P-3As, unkn, Loeing OA-1C, Douglas O-2 series, deHavilland DH-4B, Consolidated PT-1, PT-3, Boeing PW-9 and Consolidated PT-1. This image appears in Arcadia Publishing's "San Diego's North Island 1911-1941" Written by Katrina Pescador and Mark Aldrich of the San Diego Air and Space Museum. Repository: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
